#: f169af7f099743d7bc37756da7253275
msgid ""
"The Bass diffusion model, developed by Frank Bass in 1969, is a "
"mathematical model that describes how new products get adopted in a "
"population over time. It's widely used in marketing to forecast sales of "
"new products, especially when historical data is limited or non-existent."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10009
#: 8af59fde7e1449cf9c52dfc18b129879
msgid ""
"The model captures the entire lifecycle of product adoption, from "
"introduction to saturation, making it a powerful tool for product "
"planning and marketing strategy development."
msgstr ""

